             A Saudi business team is to hold
direct talks with  BP Plc , which faces a large bill for the Gulf
of Mexico oil spill,  Al Eqtisadiah  reported, without saying
where it got the information.  
 The team, including investors from the energy industry, is
seeking to acquire between 10 and 15 percent of BPâ€™s shares, the
newspaper added.  
